re|Died on 10 April}}\n| The patient had a travel history to [[Saudi Arabia]]. He was admitted to the hospital on April 7 with pneumonia symptoms and later tested positive for coronavirus. He also attended the religious congregation of Tablighi Jamaat at Nizamuddin Markaz which became a major hotspot for Covid19 in India.<ref>{{cite news |title=First Death In Assam |url=https://www.pratidintime.com/corona-first-death-in-assam/ |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=Pratidin Time |date=10 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n|}\n\n\n'''Covid-19 related deaths'''<br /> \n\nA 30-year-old migrant worker from Assam's [[Nagaon district|Nagaon]] district, who had tested positive for Coronavirus commits suicide after allegedly slitting his throat in [[Akola]] city of [[Maharashtra]] where he was undergoing treatment at a government hospital after returning from the religious congregation of Tablighi Jamaat at Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{cite news |title=Assam Tablighi Jamaat Member Commits Suicide In Maharashtra |url=https://www.pratidintime.com/covid-19-assam-tablighi-jamaat-member-commits-suicide-in-maharashtra/ |accessdate=12 April 2020 |work=Pratidin Time |date=11 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=COVID-19 PATIENT FROM ASSAM ALLEGEDLY COMMITS SUICIDE IN MAHARASHTRA |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/covid-19-patient-from-assam-allegedly-commits-suicide-in-maharashtra/ |accessdate=12 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=11 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Asia]]\n* [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n* [[2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Delhi]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://hfw.assam.gov.in/ Health & Family Welfare Ministry of Assam]\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in India by state or union territory|Assam]]\n[[Category:2020s in Assam]]