igaon district|Morigaon]]<br /> [[Nalbari district|Nalbari]]<br /> [[South Salmara district|South Salmara \u2013 Mankachar]]\n| website         = [https://covid19.assam.gov.in Covid-19 Advisory Assam]<br /> [https://covid19.assam.gov.in/all-districts/ Covid-19 Advisory Assam, Districts]\n}}\nThe first case of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed in the [[India|Indian]] state of [[Assam]] on 31 March 2020.<ref name=\":2\" /> The state has confirmed a total of 34 positive cases of [[Covid-19]] including 1 death and 12 recoveries as of {{TODAY}}.<ref name=\":12\" />\n\nThe cause of Covid-19 outbreak in Assam is due to the people who attended the religious congregation of Tablighi Jamaat at [[Nizamuddin Dargah|Nizamuddin Markaz]] and did not reported the authorities after their return to Assam.<ref name=\":60\">{{cite news |title=LIST OF 16 NIZAMUDDIN ATTENDEES WHO TEST CORONAVIRUS POSITIVE IN ASSAM |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/list-of-16-nizamuddin-attendants-who-test-coronavirus-positive-in-assam/ |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=2 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":200\" /> \nEven majority of the cases so far reported positive in Assam are rooted to the religious congregation of Tablighi Jamaat at Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{cite news |title=Two more test positive for COVID-19 in Assam; total climbs to 34 |url=https://www.businessinsider.in/india/news/two-more-test-positive-for-covid-19-in-assam-total-climbs-to-34/articleshow/75183236.cms |accessdate=18 April 2020 |work=Business Insider |date=16 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{main|Timeline of the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n[[File:Assam Government's coronavirus health advisory in Assamese.jpg|thumb|upright|left|<center>[[Coronavirus]] information poster in [[Assamese language|Assamese]]</center>]]\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/India/Assam medical cases chart}}\n=== March ===\n* The first confirmed case of coronavirus in Assam was reported on '''31 March 2020''' in [[Badarpur, Assam|Badarpur]], [[Karimganj district|Karimganj]], after a 52-year-old man returning from Delhi's Nizamuddin Markaz tested positive at Silchar Medical College.<ref>{{cite news |title=Assam's 1st Covid-19 patient visited Nizamuddin, 130 quarantined |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-assam-covid-19-patient-travelled-to-nizamuddin-1662092-2020-04-01 |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=India Today |date=1 April 2020 |author=Hemanta Kumar Nath |language=en}}</ref>\n\n===April===\n* '''On 1 April''', Four more people; 3 from [[Jagiroad]] and 1 from [[Nalbari district|Nalbari]], have been tested positive for Coronavirus at Gauhati Medical College and Hospital (GMCH), increases the toll to 5. All five patients attended Nizamuddin Markaz event in Delhi.<ref>{{cite news |title=FIVE POSITIVE CORONAVIRUS CASES IN ASSAM, ALL VISITED NIZAMUDDIN MARKAZ: HIMANTA BISWA SARMA |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/five-positive-coronavirus-cases-in-assam-all-visited-nizamuddin-markaz-himanta-biswa-sarma/ |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=1 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> On the same day, 8 more patients from [[Golaghat district|Golaghat]] were tested positive, making the toll to 13. All 13 patients attended Nizamuddin Markaz event in Delhi.<ref>{{cite news |title=Covid 19 Positive cases rises to 13 |url=https://www.pratidintime.com/assam-covid-19-positive-cases-rise-to-13/ |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=Protidin Time |date=1 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Assam COVID-19 Cases Rise To 13, All Attended Delhi Mosque Event |url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/coronavirus-assam-covid-19-cases-rise-to-13-all-attended-delhi-mosque-event-2204512 |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=NDTV |date=1 April 2020 |author=Ratnadip Choudhury |language=en}}</ref>\n* '''On 2 April''', Three more new Coronavirus positive cases have been detected in Assam. Three persons from [[Goalpara district|Goalpara]] who attended Tablighi Jamat congregation at Nizamuddin Markaz have been infected with Coronavirus. With this the total number of Coronavirus positive cases in Assam has become 16.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite news |title=3 CORONAVIRUS CASES IN GOALPARA, TOTAL NUMBER RISES TO 16 IN ASSAM |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/big-breaking-3-coronavirus-cases-in-goalpara-total-number-rises-to-16-in-assam/ |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=1 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* '''On 3 April''', Four more new Coronavirus positive cases have been detected in Assam's [[Nalbari district|Nalbari]] and [[South Salmara district|South Salmara]], all attended Nizamuddin Markaz at Delhi.<ref>{{cite news |title=Covid-19 Positive cases rise to 20 |url=https://www.pratidintime.com/assam-covid-19-positive-cases-rise-to-20/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Pratidin Time |date=3 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":200\">{{cite news |title=4 MORE COVID-19 POSITIVE CASES IN ASSAM, TOTAL CASES RISE TO 20 |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/breaking-4-more-covid-19-positive-cases-in-assam-total-cases-rise-to-20/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=3 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> On the same day, three more positive cases have been confirmed with the first case in the capital city of [[Guwahati]].<ref name=\":19\">{{cite news |title=FIRST CORONAVIRUS POSITIVE CASE IN GUWAHATI |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/first-coronavirus-positive-case-in-guwahati/ |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=4 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> Out of these, two patients are related to Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{cite news |title=THREE MORE CORONAVIRUS CASES IN ASSAM, TOTAL NUMBER RISES TO 23 |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/breaking-three-more-coronavirus-cases-in-assam-total-number-rises-to-23/ |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=3 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* '''On 4 April''', One more person has been found with Coronavirus positive in [[Golaghat district|Golaghat]] related to Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{cite news |title=ONE MORE CORONAVIRUS CASE WITH NIZAMUDDIN LINK IN GOLAGHAT, TOTAL 24 IN ASSAM |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/big-breaking-one-more-coronavirus-case-with-nizamuddin-link-in-golaghat-total-24-in-assam/ |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=4 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> On the same day, one more Covid-19 positive case has been detected in Assam's [[North Lakhimpur]], who was also an attendee of Tablighi Jamaat at Nizamuddin Markaz in Delhi.<ref>{{cite news |title=CORONAVIRUS POSITIVE CASE IN NORTH LAKHIMPUR, TOTAL NUMBER IN ASSAM RISES TO 25 |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/breaking-coronavirus-positive-case-in-north-lakhimpur-total-number-in-assam-rises-to-25/ |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=4 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> At the end of the day, another positive case registered in Assam's [[Cachar district|Cachar]] district who also attended the religious congregation at Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{cite news |title=ONE MORE COVID19 POSITIVE IN CACHAR, TOTAL 26 IN ASSAM |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/big-breaking-one-more-covid19-positive-in-cachar-total-26-in-assam/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=4 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* '''On 7 April''', One more person has been found with Coronavirus positive in [[Chapar, Dhubri|Chapar]]<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news |title=JAMALUDDIN HAZI FROM DHUBRI IS ASSAM\u2019S PATIENT NUMBER 27 |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/covid19-jamaluddin-hazi-from-dhubri-is-assams-patient-number-27/ |accessdate=8 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=7 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> at Dhubri district, which is also linked to Tablighi Jamaat of Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{cite news |title=Covid-19 positive cases in Assam increases to 27 |url=https://www.pratidintime.com/covid-19-positive-cases-in-assam-increase-to-27/ |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=Pratidin Time |date=7 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> On the same day, one more Covid-19 positive case has been detected in Assam's [[Hailakandi district|Hailakandi]] district, who has a travel history to Saudi Arabia and also linked to the Tablighi Jamaat event in Nizamuddin Markaz at New Delhi.<ref>{{cite news |title=Another positive case in Assam, count rises to 28 |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/coronavirus-another-positive-case-in-assam-count-rises-to-28/article31285623.ece |accessdate=8 April 2020 |work=The Hindu |date=8 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> Incidentally, it's the first covid-19 positive case in Assam with a travel history outside India.<ref>{{cite news |title=ONE COVID19 POSITIVE CASE IN HAILAKANDI, TOTAL NUMBER IN ASSAM RISES TO 28 |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/big-breaking-one-covid19-positive-case-in-hailakandi-total-number-in-assam-rises-to-28/ |accessdate=8 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=7 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* '''On 9 April''', One more person has been found with Coronavirus positive in [[Bilasipara]]<ref name=\":5\">{{cite news |title=One more tests COVID-19 positive in Assam\u2019s Dhubri, tally rises to 29 |url=https://northeastlivetv.com/2020/04/09/one-more-tests-covid-19-positive-in-assams-dhubri-tally-rises-to-29/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |work=Northeast Live |date=9 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> at [[Dhubri district|Dhubri]] district. The person was in contact with the positive patient from the same district. So the patient is also but indirectly related to the religious congregation at Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{cite news |title=ANOTHER COVID19 POSITIVE CASE IN DHUBRI, TOLL RISES TO 29 IN ASSAM |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/breaking-another-covid19-positive-case-in-dhurbi-toll-rises-to-29-in-assam/ |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=9 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title= One more tested positive for covid 19 in assam total 29 |url=https://www.pratidintime.com/one-more-tested-positive-for-covid-19-in-assam-total-29/ |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=Pratidin Time |date=9 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* '''On 10 April''', Assam reported its first Covid19 linked death in [[Hailakandi district|Hailakandi]] district. A 65-year-old man who had gone to Saudi Arabia and then visited Nizamuddin Markaz and who was suffering from Pneumonia too, died early this morning at [[Silchar Medical College and Hospital]].<ref>{{cite news |title=FIRST COVID19 DEATH IN ASSAM: HAILAKANDI PATIENT FAIJUL BARBHUYAN DIES |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/first-covid19-death-in-assam-hailakandi-patient-faijul-barbhuyan-dies/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=10 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Assam Records First COVID-19 Death |url=https://www.guwahatiplus.com/daily-news/assam-records-first-covid-19-death |accessdate=10 April 2020 |work=G plus |date=10 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* '''On 13 April''', One more person tested positive for Covid-19 at [[Fakhruddin Ali Ahmed Medical College and Hospital|Barpeta Medical College]] in Assam's [[Dhubri district|Dhubri]] district who is also linked to Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{cite news |title=One more tests positive for Covid-19, total rises to 30 |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/guwahati/assam-one-more-tests-positive-for-covid-19-total-rises-to-30/articleshow/75119306.cms |accessdate=14 April 2020 |work=The Times of India |date=13 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=HAJRAT ALI FROM DHUBRI IS ASSAM\u2019S 30TH COVID19 PATIENT |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/hajrat-ali-from-dhubri-is-assams-30th-covid19-patient/ |accessdate=14 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=13 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> On the same day, another patient tested positive for Covid19 from Assam's [[Goalpara district|Goalpara]] district who came in contact with a person associated with Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{cite news |title=One more tests positive for Covid-19 in Assam, count 31 |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/guwahati/one-more-tests-positive-for-covid-19-in-assam-count-31/articleshow/75134660.cms |accessdate=14 April 2020 |work=The Times of India |date=14 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Another Person from Assam's Goalpara District Tests Positive for Covid-19, State Tally Climbs to 31 |url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/man-from-assams-goalpara-district-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-state-tally-climbs-to-31-2576859.html |accessdate=14 April 2020 |work=News18 |date=14 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* '''On 14 April''', Another person tested positive for Covid-19 in [[Dhubri district|Dhubri]] district. The patient is the wife of the Covid19 positive patient who attended the religious congregation of Tablighi Jamaat at Nizamuddin Markaz and then attended the Athgaon Kabristhan mosque event which became a Covid19 hotspot in Assam.<ref>{{cite news |title=Wife of Covid-19 patient in Assam tests positive, state tally rises to 32 confirmed cases |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/wife-of-covid-19-patient-in-assam-tests-positive-state-tally-rises-to-32-confirmed-cases-1667013-2020-04-14 |accessdate=15 April 2020 |work=India Today |date=14 April 2020 |author=Hemanta Kumar Nath |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=WOMAN FROM DHUBRI TESTS COVID19 POSITIVE, TOTAL NUMBER RISES TO 32 IN ASSAM |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/breaking-woman-from-dhubri-tests-covid19-positive-total-number-rises-to-32-in-assam/ |accessdate=15 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=14 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* '''On 15 April''', Two Covid-19 patients recovered from the disease after their samples were found negative in repeated tests. The two patients were from [[Morigaon district|Morigaon]] district, both with links to the religious congregation of Tablighi Jamaat, were released from the Sonapur district hospital.<ref>{{cite news |title=First for Assam: Two Covid-19 patients recover; discharged from hospital |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/first-for-assam-two-covid-19-patients-recover-discharged-from-hospital/story-ws0OUsG3KNElQjsFPdLJfJ.html |accessdate=16 April 2020 |work=Hindustan Times |date=16 April 2020 |author=Utpal Parashar |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=TWO COVID19 PATIENTS DISCHARGED FROM SONAPUR HOSPITAL |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/assam-two-covid19-patients-discharged-from-sonapur-hospital/ |accessdate=16 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=15 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* '''On 16 April''', Two more persons of Lahorighat in [[Morigaon district|Morigaon]] district tested positive for Covid-19. The patients came in contact with a Covid19 positive patient who attended the religious congregation of Tablighi Jamaat at Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{cite news |title=Two more test positive for coronavirus in Assam; total climbs to 34 |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/assam-coronavirus-positive-cases-guwahati-covid19-news-608323 |accessdate=17 April 2020 |work=India TV |date=16 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=DC, SP, Jt Director of Health told to stay in home quarantine |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/covid-19-dc-sp-jt-director-of-health-told-to-stay-in-home-quarantine-120041601870_1.html |accessdate=17 April 2020 |work=Business Standard |date=16 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> On the same day, three Covid19 patients from [[Goalpara district|Goalpara]] district recovered from the disease and have been discharged from Goalpara Civil Hospital.<ref>{{cite news |title=Five Covid-19 patients discharged in Assam in 24 hours |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/five-covid-19-patients-discharged-in-assam-in-24-hours-1667598-2020-04-16 |accessdate=17 April 2020 |work=India Today |date=16 April 2020 |author=Hemanta Kumar Nath |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=THREE COVID19 PATIENTS DISCHARGED FROM GOALPARA CIVIL HOSPITAL |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/breaking-three-covid19-patients-discharged-from-goalpara-civil-hospital/ |accessdate=17 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=16 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* '''On 17 April''', Four more Covid-19 patients recovered from the disease after their samples were found negative in four successive tests. The four patients were from [[Golaghat district|Golaghat]] district. All four were linked with religious congregation of Tablighi Jamaat, were released from the Swahid Kushal Konwar Civil Hospital.<ref>{{cite news |title=Assam discharges four more Covid-19 patients |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/north-east/coronavirus-outbreak-assam-discharges-four-more-covid-19-patients/cid/1765755 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |work=The Telegraph |date=18 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=4 COVID19 PATIENTS DISCHARGED FROM GOLAGHAT CIVIL HOSPITAL |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/assam-4-covid19-patients-discharged-from-golaghat-civil-hospital/ |accessdate=18 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=17 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Testing==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"float:right; clear:right;\"\n|+Summary of test results\n!Samples tested\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |4,400\n|-\n!Tests per 1 million people\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |{{formatnum:{{#expr:4400/31205576*1000000 round 0}}}}\n|-\n!Tested negative\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |4,199\n|-\n!Tested positive\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |34\n|-\n!Results Awaited\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |167\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{As of|2020|April|18}}<ref>{{cite news |title=120 COVID19 TESTS PER 10 LAKH POPULATION IN STATE, SAYS HIMANTA BISWA SARMA |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/assam-120-covid19-tests-per-10-lakh-population-in-state-says-himanta-biswa-sarma/ |accessdate=18 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=18 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n|}\nAs of 18 April 2020, 4,400 Covid-19 tests so far conducted in the six laboratories in Assam, the centres are located at [[Gauhati Medical College and Hospital]], [[Assam Medical College|Assam Medical College and Hospital]], [[Silchar Medical College and Hospital]], [[Jorhat Medical College and Hospital]], [[Fakhruddin Ali Ahmed Medical College and Hospital|Barpeta Medical College and Hospital]] and [[Tezpur Medical College and Hospital]]<ref>{{cite news |title=ICMR APPROVES TEZPUR MEDICAL COLLEGE LAB FOR COVID19 TESTING |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/education/breaking-icmr-approves-tezpur-medical-college-lab-for-covid19-testing/ |accessdate=17 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=17 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=5th Lab of Assam getting Accreditation from ICMR |url=https://www.sentinelassam.com/north-east-india-news/assam-news/covid-19-testing-5th-lab-of-assam-getting-accreditation-from-icmr/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=The Sentinel |date=30 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> Initially, the labs tested samples only from those with a travel history to other countries or outside Assam designated as high-risk, or those who have come in contact with anyone testing positive for the coronavirus, or showing symptoms as per the government guidelines. In this, 4,199 samples of Covid-19 are negative, whereas 34 samples tested positive.<ref>{{cite news |title=COVID-19: 4400 Samples Collected, 34 Positive, 4199 Negative in Assam |url=https://www.guwahatiplus.com/daily-news/covid-19-4400-samples-collected-34-positive-4199-negative-in-assam |accessdate=18 April 2020 |work=G plus |date=18 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> In the total tests, 1,421 samples alone were linked with Nizamuddin markaz in which 30 samples tested positive and results of 34 are awaited.<ref>{{cite news |title=Assam Conducts 1421 Tests of People Related to Tablighi Jamaat |url=https://www.guwahatiplus.com/daily-news/covid-19-assam-conducts-1421-tests-of-people-related-to-tablighi-jamaat |accessdate=13 April 2020 |work=G plus |date=13 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=One more tests positive for coronavirus in Assam, tally in state at 31 |url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/one-more-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-in-assam-tally-in-state-at-31-825190.html |accessdate=14 April 2020 |work=Deccan Herald |date=14 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Help==\n===State relief fund===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"float:right; clear:right;\"\n|+Assam Arogya Nidhi\n!Amount Received\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |96.88 cr\n|-\n!No. of Donor\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |44,834\n|-\n!Date of Commencing\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |26-03-2020\n|-\n!Status\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |open\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{As of|2020|April|17}}<ref name=\":7\">{{cite news |title=ASSAM AROGYA NIDHI RECEIVES RS 96.88 CRORE DONATIONS |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/covid19-assam-arogya-nidhi-receives-rs-96-88-crore-donations/ |accessdate=17 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=17 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n|}\nOn 26 March 2020, Assam Government launched a state relief fund for Covid19 as ''Assam Arogya Nidhi Fund'' and sought contribution from the public to contribute to the Assam state fund, to help the state government in its battle to combat the spread of coronavirus in Assam.<ref>{{cite news |title=Over Rs 24 Cr Donated to Assam Arogya Nidhi Fund |url=https://www.guwahatiplus.com/daily-news/covid-19-over-rs-24-cr-donated-to-assam-arogya-nidhi-fund |accessdate=10 April 2020 |work=G plus |date=8 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Border with Manipur, Mizoram to be sealed: Himanta |url=https://www.thehillstimes.in/regional/border-with-manipur-mizoram-to-be-sealed-himanta/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |work=The Hills Times |date=27 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> As of 17 April 2020, more than 40,000 people have donated more than Rs 90 cr to Assam Arogya Nidhi.<ref name=\":7\" />\n\nMoreover, the Income Tax Department and the Finance Ministry has also clarified that all donations to Assam Arogya Nidhi are eligible for 100 per cent deduction since it is a donation made to state relief fund which is set up by the State Government to provide medical relief to the poor as per as Sec 80G (1).<ref>{{cite news |title=Assam Arogya Nidhi donations exempted from taxes |url=https://nenow.in/health/assam-arogya-nidhi-donations-exempted-from-taxes.html |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=Northeast now |date=9 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=ALL DONATIONS TO ASSAM AROGYA NIDHI ELIGIBLE FOR 100 PERCENT EXEMPTION FROM INCOME TAX |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/covid19-all-donations-to-assam-arogya-nidhi-eligible-for-100-percent-exemption-from-income-tax/ |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=9 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nMany well known businessmen, social activists, government employees, sports personalities, religious trusts and even common people have contributed a huge donation to Assam Arogya Nidhi. Well known Guwahati based businessman and social activist ''Anand Kumar Jain'' has donated over Rs 2 crore as a support towards the fight against coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |title=Guwahati Based Businessman Donates Over Rs 2 Cr to Fight Coronavirus |url=https://www.guwahatiplus.com/daily-news/guwahati-based-businessman-donates-over-rs-2-cr-to-fight-coronavirus |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=G plus |date=9 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> Three other businessmen from Assam have also contributed a huge amount to strengthen the fight against Covid19. Among them, ''Anil Das'' donated Rs 50 lakh, ''Anupam Sarma'' donated Rs 25 lakh and ''Aditya Goswami'' donated Rs 21 lakh towards Assam State relief fund.<ref>{{cite news |title=THREE ASSAM BUSINESSMEN DONATE RS 1 CRORE 46 LAKH |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/assam/covid19-three-assam-businessmen-donate-rs-1-crore-46-lakh/ |accessdate=12 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=5 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> The ''Kamakhya Devalaya'' also contributed Rs. 5 lakh to the Assam Arogya Nidhi to boost up the fight against the outbreak of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kamakhya Devalaya extends Rs 5 lakh to Assam Arogya Nidhi Scheme to fight against COVID-19 |url=https://www.sentinelassam.com/guwahati-city/kamakhya-devalaya-extends-rs-5-lakh-to-assam-arogya-nidhi-scheme-to-fight-against-covid-19/ |accessdate=13 April 2020 |work= The Sentinel |date=1 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> Asian Games gold medallist [[Hima Das]] has donated her one month's salary to Assam state fund.<ref>{{cite news |title=Hima Das donates one month's salary to Assam government |url=https://www.mykhel.com/more-sports/coronavirus-hima-das-donates-a-month-s-salary-to-assam-govt-140685.html |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=My Khel |date=27 March 2020 |author=Sajith B Warrier |language=en}}</ref> ''Reema Ghosh'', a college student from Assam's Rangia has donated Rs 1.93 lakh to Assam Arogya Nidhi, which her parents were saving for her marriage.<ref>{{cite news |title=Assam student donates nearly Rs 2 lakh to state Covid-19 relief fund |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/assam-student-donates-nearly-rs-2-lakh-to-state-covid-19-relief-fund-1663833-2020-04-06 |accessdate=13 April 2020 |work=India Today |date=6 April 2020 |author=Hemanta Kumar Nath |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Hotspot==\nThe Assam government has identified ''Athgaon Kabristhan mosque'' in [[Guwahati]] as a COVID-19 hotspot and closed it down for two weeks after three persons tested positive for coronavirus who attended a recent meeting there of over 100 people on March 12, in which some returnees from the religious congregation of Tablighi Jamaat at Nizamuddin Markaz ''(Covid19 hotspot in India)''<ref>{{cite news |title=Health Ministry Identifies Ten COVID-19 \u2018Hotspots\u2019 Across India |url=https://weather.com/en-IN/india/coronavirus/news/2020-04-01-health-ministry-identifies-ten-covid-hotspot-across-india |accessdate=12 April 2020 |work=weather.com |date=1 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> also took part.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mosque where 3 Covid-19 positive people stayed; first death in Assam linked to Jamaat meet |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/mosque-where-3-covid-19-positive-people-stayed-first-death-in-assam-linked-to-jamaat-meet-1665741-2020-04-11 |accessdate=12 April 2020 |work=India Today |date=11 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=ASSAM\u2019S COVID19 HOTSPOT ATHGAON MASJID SEALED, DECLARED CONTAINMENT ZONE |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/guwahati-assams-covid19-hotspot-athgaon-masjid-sealed-declared-containment-zone/ |accessdate=12 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=10 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable mw-collapsible\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%; width:600px; clear:right; margin:0px 0px 0.5em 1em;\"\n! colspan=\"7\" |{{resize|110%|{{Nowrap|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Assam by districts}}}}\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" |S.No.\n! scope=\"col\" |District\n! scope=\"col\" |Active Cases\n! scope=\"col\" |Recovered\n! scope=\"col\" |Deaths\n! scope=\"col\" |Total Cases\n! scope=\"col\" |Places\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |1\n| [[Cachar district|Cachar]]\n| 0\n| 1\n| 0\n| 1\n| \n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |2\n| [[Dhubri district|Dhubri]]\n| 4\n| 0\n| 0\n| 4\n| [[Chapar, Dhubri|Chapar]] (1)<ref name=\":1\" /> [[Bilasipara]] (1)<ref name=\":5\" />\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |3\n| [[Goalpara district|Goalpara]]\n| 1\n| 3\n| 0\n| 4\n| \n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |4\n| [[Golaghat district|Golaghat]]\n| 5\n| 4\n| 0\n| 9\n| [[Dergaon]] (2) [[Morangi]] (2) [[Merapani]] (4)<ref name=\":60\" />\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |5\n| [[Hailakandi district|Hailakandi]]\n| 0\n| 0\n| 1\n| 1\n| \n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |6\n| [[Kamrup district|Kamrup]]\n| 1\n| 0\n| 0\n| 1\n| [[Boko, Kamrup|Boko]] (1)<ref>{{cite news |title=MAJOR ANNOUNCEMENTS BY HIMANTA BISWA SARMA ON SATURDAY |url=https://www.newslivetv.com/top-news/assam-covid19-major-announcements-by-himanta-biswa-sarma-on-saturday/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=News Live |date=4 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |7\n| [[Kamrup Metropolitan district|Kamrup Metropolitan]]\n| 1\n| 0\n| 0\n| 1\n| [[Guwahati]] (1)<ref name=\":19\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |8\n| [[Karimganj district|Karimganj]]\n| 1\n| 0\n| 0\n| 1\n| [[Badarpur, Assam|Badarpur]] (1)\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |9\n| [[Lakhimpur district|Lakhimpur]]\n| 1\n| 0\n| 0\n| 1\n| [[North Lakhimpur]] (1)<ref>{{cite news |title=Covid-19 Positive case rise to 25 |url=https://www.pratidintime.com/assam-covid-19-positive-cases-rise-to-25/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=Pratidin Time |date=4 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |10\n| [[Morigaon district|Morigaon]]\n| 4\n| 2\n| 0\n| 6\n| [[Jagiroad]] (3) Lahorighat (1)<ref>{{cite news |title=DC, SP, Jt Director of Health told to stay in home quarantine |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/covid19-dc-sp-jt-director-of-health-told-to-stay-in-home-quarantine/1805077 |accessdate=17 April 2020 | work=Outlook India |date=16 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |11\n| [[Nalbari district|Nalbari]]\n| 2\n| 2\n| 0\n| 4\n| \n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |12\n| [[South Salmara district|South Salmara- Mankachar]]\n| 1\n| 0\n| 0\n| 1\n| South Salmara (1)<ref name=\":200\" />\n|-\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n! colspan=\"2\" | Total\n! scope=\"col\" | 21\n! scope=\"col\" | 12\n! scope=\"col\" | 1\n! 34\n!\n|- class=\"sortbottom\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| colspan=\"7\" |<small>As of {{TODAY}}</small><ref name=\":4\" />\n|}\n\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n  |height = 250\n  |width = 650\n  |type = line\n  | yGrid =\n  | xGrid =\n  |showValues =\n  |showSymbols=1\n  |legend =\n  |colors = #FF6347,#FFC000,#87CEEB,#343132\n  |xAxisTitle = Date\n  |xAxisAngle = -40\n  |yAxisTitle = Count\n  |y1Title = Total confirmed cases\n  |y2Title = Active cases\n  |y3Title = Recoveries\n  |y4Title = Deaths\n  |yAxisMin = 0\n  |x = 31 Mar, 1 Apr, 2 Apr, 3 Apr, 4 Apr, 5 Apr, 6 Apr, 7 